The reason Gamma radiation penetrates matter so easily is simply because it rarely reacts with the matter (save for high-density metals, such as lead) it's passing through. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.whitetoweronline.com"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.whitetoweronline.com/hall/icons/barth-sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sovin>Sovin</A> at: 4/5/03 9:49:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sovin>Sovin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tachyon Wrangler</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(4/5/03 9:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.whitetoweronline.com/hall/images/offedge.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Would Orion Really Work?</span><hr size=1> It's getting on in the eve..  No-one's around or posting..and I'm bored..So, y'all will just have to deal with another post from me.. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
